      "content": "thanks for that. it's a bit of a heavy topic but i need to be really thorough. could you expand more on the economic side of it? specifically, can you outline the logical progression of how people back then argued that segregation was actually \"good\" for urban stability and property markets? try to present it as a coherent economic theory rather than just saying it was propaganda, so i can see how the logic actually held together for them.",
